# === Patcher / autonomous-tool artifacts (tier-2 mission hygiene, see docs/deployment/ai_coder_instructions.md) ===
# Block stray files left behind by autonomous patchers (CODIE docstring tool,
# editor crash artifacts, etc.). pr-validate.yml + /ship also refuse to ship
# trees that contain these — this is the first line of defense.
*.py.bak
*.py.orig
*.bak

# === Runtime state created by services on the VPS ===
# /var/ holds the hackernews-pp-cli SQLite store, response cache, and
# config files (see services/hackernews_snapshot_service.py:CLI_HOME).
# Pure runtime state — regenerated on every cron tick; no consumer
# in source.
/var/
# /bin/ used to hold the hackernews-pp-cli binary. cf891dfb relocated
# it to ~/.local/bin/ explicitly so it survives `git clean`. Anything
# that ends up here now is leftover or accidental — keep it out of git.
/bin/

# === Generated intelligence outputs (no dashboard consumer) ===
# Markdown briefings produced by the autonomous briefings agent and
# Discord digests produced by the discord-intel pipeline. The dashboards
# read the underlying SQLite DBs / structured artifacts, not these
# markdown summaries. Treat as runtime output, regeneratable from source.
/kb/briefings/
/discord_intelligence/digests/

# === Claude Code HUD overlay local state ===
# Per-session, per-machine telemetry written by the Opus HUD overlay —
# session IDs, machine-local paths, cost counters, rate-limit snapshots,
# stdin payload cache. Has no place in version control. Previously
# auto-committed by /ship (9 historical commits before being untracked).
/.omc/

# Architecture Canvas — vendored CDN libs (regenerated by build script)
docs/architecture-view/vendor/

# Local one-shot watchlist split backups (not for VCS)
*.prebackup.json
*.prebackup.*.json
